        .content
            section
                h2 Features
                ul.list
                    li Use your own markup, event names, classes, selectors etc. 
                    li Scroll vertically or horizontally, infinitely or finitely.
                    li Auto play, pause, stop.
                    li Auto generate "dots" or configure your own.
                    li Scroll multiple items, or just one.
                    li Add and remove items via the API.
                    li Auto fill max width of browser, auto scale the height too, or don't.
                    li Arrow key navigation. 
                    li Use touch events when possible, or don't.
                    li Supports orientation change in maxwidth mode.

            section
                h2 Setup 

                p
                    a(href="dist/jcarrotcell.zip", class="cc-download") Download 
                    | the jCarrotCell bundle or clone the repo from  
                    a(href="https://github.com/yujulia/jCarrotCell", class="cc-github", target="_blank") Github
                    |.
                p
                    | You will need to include some version of 
                    a(href="https://jquery.com/" target="_blank") jQuery 
                    | (version 1.7+) before 
                    strong jCarrotCell.js 
                    | and also the styles from  
                    strong carrotcell.css
                    | .

                p 
                    | The markup should look something like this, see the 
                    a(href="", class="cc-files") Documentation 
                    | on how to use whatever markup you want.

                pre: code(data-language="html").
                    <ol class="my-thing">
                        <li>item 1</li>
                        <li>item 2</li>
                        <li>item 3</li>
                    </ol>       

                p Invoke the carrotcell with the following:

                pre: code(data-language="js").
                    $(".my-thing").carrotCell();

